article.headline: Houston 89, Monmouth 80
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Oliver Lafayette scored a team-high 29 points to lead the Houston Cougars to an 89-80 win over the Monmouth Hawks on Saturday. Despite fouling out with just over two minutes left in the game, Lafayette led the Cougars to their second straight win by making eight of his 19 shots including a team-high five three-pointers. Robert McIver added five three-pointers and scored 25 points for the Cougars who led by nine, 47-38, at halftime. No other Houston player reached double-digits, although three players -- Robert Lee (9), Marcus Malone (8) and Jahmar Thorpe (8) -- scored at least eight. Dejan Delic was the best offensive player on the floor and scored a game-high 33 points for the Hawks, who fell to 1-3 on the year. Delic, who was the team's leading scorer a year ago, made 10 of his 14 shots from the floor, including six of nine from beyond the three point line. The only other Hawks to score in double-digits were Marques Alston with 15 and Jhamar Youngblood with 12. After trailing by 13 in the first half, the Hawks rallied to tie the game with 11:18 left when Youngblood made a layup after stealing the ball from the Cougars. But Houston pushed the lead back with a 7-1 run over the next six minutes led by Lafayette's five points. The Cougars were outshot in the game as Monmouth made 46 percent of their shots from the floor (26-for-57) to the Cougars' 39-percent (30-for-77). But Houston had 28 points off turnovers and allowed just 19.
